# Backend-only package: no UI, no Node/pnpm build at .deb build time.
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), build-essential
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/Rushikesh-Palande/hermes

Package: hermes-backend
# Pure Python source — Architecture: all works on amd64 and arm64.
# The platform-specific venv is built at install time by
# packaging/install.sh (postinst → install.sh --skip-ui).
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3.11,
         python3-venv,
         postgresql-16,
         timescaledb-2-postgresql-16,
         mosquitto,
         adduser
# nginx is Recommends here: the API listens on :8080 directly, so nginx
# is not required. Operators running a custom frontend or reverse proxy
# can omit it.
Recommends: nginx, certbot, python3-certbot-nginx
Description: HERMES backend — industrial sensor ingest + REST API (no UI)
 HERMES ingests 12-channel ADC telemetry from STM32 hardware over MQTT
 at ~100 Hz per sensor, runs four parallel event-detection algorithms
 (A/B/C/D + BREAK mode transition), persists events with +-9 s context
 windows to TimescaleDB, and exposes the full dataset via a REST API.
 .
 This is the API-only package without the SvelteKit operator dashboard.
 Use it when integrating HERMES with a custom frontend, a third-party
 visualisation tool, or a SCADA / PLC system consuming events over MQTT.
 The full stack (API + dashboard) is in the hermes package.
 .
 After install:
 .
   * API:   http://<host>:8080/api/health
   * Docs:  http://<host>:8080/docs  (Swagger UI)
   * Logs:  journalctl -u hermes-api -u hermes-ingest -f
 .
 See /opt/hermes/docs/customer/INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md for the complete
 API reference, authentication guide, and integration examples.
